(GHSA-76w7-j9cq-rx2j / CVE-2026-47208 / AIKIDO-2026-10842) — "close Promise
species hijack in localPromise swallow tail" — adapted for vm2 3.9.17.

vm2 3.9.17 does not have the localPromise subclass / swallow-tail / cached
globalPromisePrototypeThen / resetPromiseSpecies helper that the upstream
one-line fix edits (all introduced by the GHSA-hw58-p9xv-2mjh Promise-
hardening subsystem in the 3.10.x/3.11.x line). The upstream context does
not exist in 3.9.17, so the fix is adapted to target's simpler Promise
sanitization: a Proxy over Promise.prototype.then that eventually invokes
the host then via `localReflectApply(target, thiz, args)`. That call site
is the analogue of upstream's swallow-tail — the host then reads
`this.constructor[Symbol.species]` and `Construct`s the downstream child.
A sandbox subclass that overrides `Symbol.species` to a user function
captures V8's internal (resolve, reject) capability, and combined with a
deep-recursion RangeError from `e.stack` inside `PromiseResolveThenableJob`
delivers a raw host-realm Error to sandbox code — the sandbox can then
reach the host `Function` constructor via `.constructor.constructor`,
yielding RCE.

Fix (adapted for 3.9.17): before every host then invocation performed by
the sandbox's Promise-sanitization proxy, pin `this.constructor` to a
non-hijackable value using an own data property (mirroring upstream's
resetPromiseSpecies). The AsyncErrorHandler (`!allowAsync`) branch does
not call host then at all — it throws unconditionally — so no additional
change is needed there. Also brings in the paired regression test
`test/ghsa/GHSA-76w7-j9cq-rx2j/repro.js` from the upstream fix commit
verbatim; it self-defines `it.cond` when missing (mocha in 3.9.17's dev
deps does not ship it), and gates the canonical PoC on
`Promise.withResolvers` (Node 22+) — older Node versions skip the PoC test
but still exercise the two species-hijack variants and the benign-
subclass regression check, which do not need withResolvers.

Files intentionally NOT included from the upstream commit:
  - CHANGELOG.md — upstream diff edits a v3.11.4 changelog entry that
    does not exist in 3.9.17 (would fuzz-fail).
  - docs/ATTACKS.md — the docs/ directory does not exist in 3.9.17.

